Job.create!([
  {title: "Head of Finance", job_type: "contract", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 450, description: "<span style=\"font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: black;\">Our client is a start up e-commerce business already making great waves in its sector. They have raised significant funds and have been trading and growing for a year now. </span>\n<p style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; word-spacing: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: black;\">The CEO is now looking for someone to help drive the business forwards to the next stage financially, and long term the next round of fund raising.</span></p>He needs someone to help him look at their profitability, margins, investor reports, and understand the levers for their business. You will work with the marketing teams, sales and ops, and the board, and put together a new set of reports that will provide the information to help the business maximise its potential. However, you are the only person in finance so will also be required to run the month end, submit VAT returns, and more core finance activities along those lines.\n\nThe ideal candidate will be/have:\n<ul>\n \t<li>highly commercial and able to design, standardise and draft financial reports for the board and investors</li>\n \t<li>strong modelling experience in a growing business</li>\n \t<li>experience of implementing new systems and processes</li>\n \t<li>track record of driving commercial value and increased margins/EBITDA</li>\n \t<li>worked in core finance having filed VAT returns, performed balance sheet reconciliations, run month end, etc.</li>\n \t<li>experience of a SME environment, but also understand best practice process from audit or blue chip environments</li>\n</ul>\nThe role is based in London, is an immediate start, and runs for 4 months initially.\n\nThis is a business in a very exciting growth phase and if this sounds like something you want to be part of and feel you can help the business grow, please send your CV.", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "HS004"},
  {title: "Finance Business Partner", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Infrastructure & Prof. Services", salary: 55000, description: "Global Accounting Network has partnered with a boutique trading company in South East London to secure the latest addition to their growing team – a Finance Business Partner within the Business Development division.This is an excellent opportunity for an ambitious accountant to come into a newly created role and make it their own, with a broad set of responsibilities to deliver on, and a longer-term view of building a team around this position.\n\nThe role is split into two main components; looking after a small portfolio of companies, and working on analysis and due diligence for investments opportunities.\n<ul>\n \t<li>End to end accounting for a small collection of start-up businesses</li>\n \t<li>VAT return completion</li>\n \t<li>Coordination with central finance department over group recharges and reconciliations for intercompany balances and group accounts consolidations</li>\n \t<li>Budgeting &amp; forecasting</li>\n \t<li>Presenting senior leadership team with financial information and updates</li>\n \t<li>Due diligence &amp; analysis for investment opportunities</li>\n</ul>\nSuccessful candidates will match all, or most of the following\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant</li>\n \t<li>Experienced ownership of management accounts in an SME environment</li>\n \t<li>Strong analytical and modelling skills</li>\n \t<li>Experience with Sage (preferably X3)</li>\n \t<li>Experience completing and submitting VAT returns</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "South East London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "AB006"},
  {title: "Finance Manager - Media Start up, Central London", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 55000, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently recruiting a Finance Manager for a start-up Media business based in Central London. My client has grown quickly over the past couple of years and are forecasting further growth. They are looking to bring in a Finance Manager to help deliver this, and to enable further growth.This is a broad role, and is a true “top to bottom” finance position, with the individual being responsible for providing finance support to the founders of the business with regard to decision making, but also, as an example, chasing debtor payments.\n\nSome of the responsibilities for this position include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Day to day running of the finance function</li>\n \t<li>Preparation of monthly management accounts</li>\n \t<li>Preparation of budget and monitoring cost and revenue against</li>\n \t<li>Cash flow forecasting</li>\n \t<li>Establishing robust and efficient controls</li>\n \t<li>Financial modelling</li>\n \t<li>Business partnering with non-finance areas of the business</li>\n</ul>\nThe ideal profile for this individual will be:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant – ACA, ACCA or CIMA</li>\n \t<li>Someone with a desire to work in a fast paced, fast growth, start-up environment</li>\n \t<li>Technically strong, but also commercially minded</li>\n</ul>\nThis is great role for someone who wants to be working in a start-up environment, and is excited about helping to grow a business from an early stage where their decisions and contributions will help to build and define a company.", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "AM005"},
  {title: "FP&A Analyst", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 52000, description: "Our client is a FTSE100 Technology business that is looking for an FP&amp;A Analyst to join their high growth company. If you are looking to join a high growth business with a start-up culture, then this could be your new challenge.The FP&amp;A Analyst role is forward looking and focused on building up and maintaining relationships with finance and non-finance senior stakeholders.\n\n<strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Work closely with the Financial control team/Business support to implement improvements in the month end processes and enhance the quality of reporting and controls to necessary standards</li>\n \t<li>Be a key contributor to the forecast/ budget cycles and 5-year plan</li>\n \t<li>Support Head of FP&amp;A in all aspects of Financial Planning, Reporting and Analysis</li>\n \t<li>Improve analytical tools to provide better driver/variance/trend analysis at customer, product and transaction levels</li>\n \t<li>Timely production of the monthly management reporting packs</li>\n \t<li>Contribute towards the success of the FP&amp;A team by developing and driving month end/forecast processes to support the business deliver double digit EBITDA growth</li>\n \t<li>Owning the collation and review of monthly commentary</li>\n \t<li>Implement processes</li>\n \t<li>Ad-hoc queries</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Who are we looking for?</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant (ACA, CIMA, ACCA or international equivalent)</li>\n \t<li>Knowledge of the month end close process</li>\n \t<li>Experienced gained in a business FP&amp;A function</li>\n \t<li>Experience in a complex, high volume global business</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "GR-FPA"},
  {title: "Financial Controller", job_type: "contract", sector: "Property & Facility Management", salary: 375, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently partnering with an international real estate development business in their search for a Financial Controller on an interim basis.\n\nThe business is growing rapidly as the development enters the next phase. This is a brilliant opportunity for an individual to work within a global organisation and add some real value whilst they look for the long term permanent candidate.This role will report directly into the FD/CFO and will be responsible for the management of the accounts on behalf of the business. It will be managing a team of 5 with a view to developing the internal talent and driving continuous improvements.\n\nMain Responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Oversee the Accounting function</li>\n \t<li>Manage the month end function</li>\n \t<li>Deliver 20+ sets of annual accounts</li>\n \t<li>Spearhead a project to tidy up existing records</li>\n \t<li>Produce the consolidated quarterly management accounts</li>\n \t<li>Produce the annual accounts and liaise with the auditors</li>\n \t<li>Challenge existing accounting processes and financial controls</li>\n</ul>\nIdeal Candidates:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified Accountant</li>\n \t<li>Ideally 2+ Years in similar role</li>\n \t<li>Must speak Mandarin</li>\n \t<li>Previous management experience</li>\n \t<li>Prior experience within Commercial Real Estate or Property Development</li>\n \t<li>Strong technical and year end experience</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "East London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CH011"},
  {title: "French Speaking Management Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 65000, description: "We are recruiting for a retailer looking for a French speaking management accountant. The role will pay £60,000-65,000 + Bonus + Bens. The business is still an SME, but has an amazing product stocked in many stand alone stores around the world and also in concessions like John Lewis and Harrods.Based close to Oxford Circus, this person will be involved in the following responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Budgeting, forecasting and reporting for the group</li>\n \t<li>Design and produce monthly management reporting packs</li>\n \t<li>Product &amp; channel profitability reporting</li>\n \t<li>Pricing analysis</li>\n \t<li>Business partner to marketing / sales teams</li>\n \t<li>Cash flow forecasting and reporting</li>\n \t<li>Advise CFO on all management accounting matters</li>\n \t<li>Ad hoc reporting</li>\n</ul>\nThe ideal candidate will be a qualified ACCA/CIMA/ACA accountant with exposure to retail, manufacturing or FMCG. They must speak French and be able to start in a relatively short space of time. They must also have strong budgeting, forecasting and analysis skills. This is a highly commercial position - Please get in touch with us asap.\n\n&nbsp;", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "DL002"},
  {title: "Project Controller", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 60000, description: "Always wanted to work in that fast paced start up environment? Help set up a finance department and be part of an international growth?Our client is looking for an ACA qualified Project Controller who has both a technical and commercial background to help roll out their new company in London and in some of the biggest cities in Europe.\n\nThe company's history goes back a few years, but they are expanding their business with new projects. This is one of them. This person will play the key role in setting up the required financial systems, processes and controls for this new venture. In addition, this person will help set financial and operational KPI's as well as create and produce the management information reports needed by the senior leadership team to manage the business.\n\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA/ACCA qualified, either from practice or gained through industry</li>\n \t<li>Willing to roll up sleeves and get hands dirty in a start-up environment</li>\n \t<li>Great at building relationships with business partners and working in teams to deliver results</li>\n</ul>\nAre you hands on, a quick learner, and ready for an amazing new opportunity?\n\nThen get in touch quickly.", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "GR010"},
  {title: "Director, Corporate Finance – Transactions", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Infrastructure & Prof. Services", salary: 120000, description: "Our client is a global business advisory firm, in search of a Director, Corporate Finance - Transactions.\n\nThe Corporate Finance team plays a key role in the company and has particular experience in the Consumer sector including Tourism, Hospitality, Leisure, and Retail.<strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Managing the day to day responsibilities for transactions and other projects</li>\n \t<li>Managing the production and review of complex financial models for transactions</li>\n \t<li>Reviewing and critically analysing sets of financial accounts</li>\n \t<li>Undertaking valuations of businesses</li>\n \t<li>Conducting negotiations</li>\n \t<li>Maintaining and building a client network</li>\n \t<li>Playing a lead role in business development initiatives in specific sectors</li>\n \t<li>Overseeing and directing client meetings</li>\n \t<li>Assisting the senior team with the development and implementation of strategic plans</li>\n \t<li>Assisting in practice development projects</li>\n \t<li>Playing a key role in the management of the team including resourcing &amp; recruitment</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Background &amp; Qualifications:</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA or ACCA qualified with first time passes</li>\n \t<li>Coming from a leading practice firm</li>\n \t<li>6 years + of post qualification proven experience in Corporate Finance</li>\n \t<li>Proven track record of managing transactions</li>\n \t<li>Experience of both mainstream and complex or special situations in M&amp;A transactions</li>\n \t<li>Degree qualified (2.1 or above) and a minimum of 320 UCAS points</li>\n \t<li>Strong Microsoft Office skills essential; in particular Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Get in touch if you believe you fit the right profile for this opportunity.</strong>\n\n&nbsp;", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "GR-DCF"},
  {title: "Finance Manager", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Infrastructure & Prof. Services", salary: 55000, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently recruiting a Finance Manager role for a Global PR/Marketing business based in Central London.\n\nThis role presents a fantastic opportunity of autonomy and ownership - a sole charge role reporting to the global finance team CFO, who is based in the US.Some of the responsibilities for this position include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Support European MD on financial matters including pricing, contracts and other ad hoc requirements</li>\n \t<li>Prepare annual budgets, forecasts and variance analysis</li>\n \t<li>Prepare UK financial reporting including internal management reporting and external/statutory reporting which will include VAT Returns</li>\n \t<li>Manage cash flow, vendor payments, credit card management and Credit Control</li>\n \t<li>You will oversee external accounting advisors and processes. Including annual audit</li>\n</ul>\nThe ideal profile for this individual will be:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant – ACA, ACCA or CIMA</li>\n \t<li>Experienced in all aspects of finance</li>\n</ul>\nThis is a fantastic opportunity for someone looking to make a step into a role which has true ownership. You will be part of a tight knit team based in London where the culture is fantastic.\n\nIf you are interested in hearing more about the opportunity please get in touch.\n\n&nbsp;", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "JC-FM"},
  {title: "Finance Operations Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 55000, description: "We are actively seeking a Finance Operations Accountant to work for a thriving International Technology business.\n\nThis is a fantastic opportunity to join an energetic and innovative team. This role will report to the Finance Operations Manager.<strong><u>Key responsibilities will include- </u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Revenue and financial accounting across multiple entities</li>\n \t<li>Billing and contract analysis</li>\n \t<li>Monthly revenue based balance sheet reconciliations</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Aged debt position and supporting the collections team in the timely receipt of debts</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Business partnering to improve business operations and customer experience</li>\n \t<li>Driving system, process and control improvements throughout the finance function</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><u>Technical background- </u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>This could be an ACA/ACCA/CIMA</li>\n \t<li>Be accurate with a strong attention to detail</li>\n \t<li>Inquisitive with effective communication skills</li>\n \t<li>Adaptable and driven approach</li>\n \t<li>Confident with stakeholder engagement</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "JC015"},
  {title: "Chief Financial Officer", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 130000, description: "<span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: black;\">Global Accounting Network is partnering with a really exciting tech start-up - in search of their new finance leader. This business has an innovative and unique product set, which will enable retailers, manufacturers and logistics firms to generate significant improvements in profits.</span>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12.0pt; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; word-spacing: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Open Sans'; color: black;\">If you're an experienced CFO, then you will know what to expect - it's a top to bottom role to help the company go through their first fund raising and growth. </span></p><strong>Responsibilities will include but not be limited to:</strong>Business partnering an incredibly high calibre board\n<ul>\n \t<li>Preparing a best in class suite of management reports</li>\n \t<li>Helping to secure Series A investment in 2018</li>\n \t<li>Oversight of all reporting - management, financial and statutory</li>\n \t<li>Business planning to drive revenue and deliver growth</li>\n \t<li>Managing all aspects of finance and accounting</li>\n \t<li>Acting as the guardian of risk, implementing controls, cash management, driving rigour</li>\n</ul>\nThe <strong>ideal candidate</strong> will fit most or all of the below profile:\n<ul>\n \t<li>An experienced early stage business CFO</li>\n \t<li>Experienced and adept at raising finance from PE / VC houses</li>\n \t<li>Excellent in person with strong communication skills and a commercial outlook</li>\n \t<li>Entrepreneurial mindset</li>\n \t<li>Strong core finance skills and a hands on attitude</li>\n \t<li>Background in high tech or SAAS businesses\n\nThis role will give you the opportunity to get into something at a really early stage and add value in the company's development. We are looking for someone with the right attitude and who's willing to go the extra mile. Apply today for immediate interview.</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "GR-CFO"},
  {title: "Management Reporting Analyst", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Mining, Energy & Oil & Gas", salary: 55000, description: "Our client is in search of a Management Reporting Analyst who will ideally be a newly qualified accountant from a top 10 practice. As the Management reporting accountant, you will take primary responsibility for the production of monthly management information and reports and will be closely involved in all budgeting aspects for the Organisation and working closely with key stakeholders in the monthly maintenance of their budgets.<strong>Key responsibilities will include but are not limited to: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Preparation and analysis of the monthly Management Accounts</li>\n \t<li>Prepare year-end files for the auditors and assist with year-end schedules and reconciliations</li>\n \t<li>Assist the Group Finance Manager during the audit process</li>\n \t<li>Assist the Group Finance Manager during the budgeting and reforecasting process</li>\n</ul>\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>The ideal candidate will have the majority of the below</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA/ACCA/CIMA qualified</li>\n \t<li>Good academics</li>\n \t<li>Strong Excel skills</li>\n \t<li>In-depth experience of handling budgeting and audit processes</li>\n</ul>\nIf you are a newly qualified accountant in practice doing audit on large matrix organisations then this is an ideal opportunity for you to get into industry and work for a global organisation and add value to your career.", responsibilities: nil, location: "West End", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0020"},
  {title: "Finance Manager", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 55000, description: "We are actively seeking a Finance Manager to work for a growing Media business in Central London.\n\nThis is a fantastic opportunity to join a privately-owned business where you can truly have an impact. This role will report to the Head of FP&amp;A.\n\nThe culture at this business is incredible- a company that truly values its staff. The moment you enter their office you get an idea of their fun working environment whilst being focused on continuous growth and success.K<strong><u>ey responsibilities will include- </u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Preparing Management Accounts</li>\n \t<li>Business partnering</li>\n \t<li>Assisting with the streamlining of reporting process</li>\n \t<li>Balance sheet reconciliations and providing analysis</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><u>Technical background- </u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>This could be an ACA/ACCA/ CIMA</li>\n \t<li>Be accurate with a strong attention to detail</li>\n \t<li>Inquisitive with effective communication skills</li>\n \t<li>Adaptable and driven approach</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "JC01251"},
  {title: "Senior FP&A Analyst", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 75000, description: "Are you an experienced Qualified FP&amp;A Analyst with proven track record of providing detailed financial analysis and financial modelling within a creative setting and familiar with working in a data intensive environment. We are partnering with a dynamic marketing agency on this newly created role who are looking for an experienced Senior FP&amp;A analyst to support with strategic and continued growth.Key responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Assist in designing and creation of revenue generation and job costing reporting systems</li>\n \t<li>Financial planning - 5 year plans, annual budgets, quarterly/ year forecasts, P&amp;L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow</li>\n \t<li>Prep financial reports, charts, tables and other ad hoc projects as required</li>\n \t<li>Projects to improve process efficiency and performance</li>\n \t<li>Reporting and analysis of results or performance against historical, budgeted, forecasted and strategic planning results to support decision making</li>\n \t<li>Financial modelling, maintain models during planning process ensuring accuracy and focused analytical review</li>\n</ul>\nKey requirements:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified Accountant - ACA, CIMA, ACCA, minimum 5 years post qualification experience</li>\n \t<li>Minimum experience of 5 years in an FP&amp;A Analyst role</li>\n \t<li>Experience in working in a data intensive environment</li>\n \t<li>Advanced Excel Skills</li>\n \t<li>Excellent English written and verbal communication skills</li>\n \t<li>Discreet, mature and profession approach</li>\n</ul>\nA fantastic opportunity to join a well-established business in a newly created role that will allow you to really put your stamp on it. If you have all that is required and believe that you are up to the challenge then please apply now.", responsibilities: nil, location: "Berkshire", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0022"},
  {title: "Commercial Finance Analyst - 6-9 month contract", job_type: "contract", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 350, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently partnering with a global travel business who are at the beginning of an exciting journey as they have recently been purchased by another PE backed business.\n\nThis is a newly created role which will sit within the Commercial Finance team and report into both the Finance Business Partner and the Head of Commercial.\n\nThe role has been designed to support the operations finance business partner with analysis and the production of new business cases. In addition to the business partner this position will have exposure across the business and various departments.Main responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Build and maintain strong relationships both within finance and the wider business</li>\n \t<li>Produce weekly and monthly reporting on the performance of the business</li>\n \t<li>Assist in the creation of new business cases for multiple divisions</li>\n \t<li>Provide support where possible on the reporting, budgeting, forecasting and general finance activities</li>\n \t<li>Act as the lead business partner when required</li>\n \t<li>Provide assistance to the wider commercial finance team on new projects</li>\n</ul>\nIdeal Candidate:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Fully qualified accountant</li>\n \t<li>Experience in a similar role with commercial analysis and business partnering</li>\n \t<li>Strong Modelling and excel skills</li>\n \t<li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CH0231"},
  {title: "Financial Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Property & Facility Management", salary: 50000, description: "We are actively seeking a Financial Accountant to work for a well- established property business in Central London\n\n&nbsp;K<strong><u>ey responsibilities will include:</u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Responsible for all financial accounting and reporting for two portfolio clients</li>\n \t<li>Production of statutory financial statements</li>\n \t<li>Point of contact for external auditors</li>\n \t<li>Proficient knowledge of UK GAAP</li>\n \t<li>Balance sheet reconciliations</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><u>Technical background:</u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>This could be an ACA/ACCA/</li>\n \t<li>Be accurate with a strong attention to detail</li>\n \t<li>Inquisitive with effective communication skills</li>\n \t<li>Adaptable and driven approach</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><u>Soft Skills</u></strong>\n\nThe successful candidate will be;\n<ul>\n \t<li>Articulate</li>\n \t<li>Professional</li>\n \t<li>Effective communication skills</li>\n \t<li>Proactive and organised</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "JC01252"},
  {title: "Financial Controller - 9 month contract", job_type: "contract", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 450, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently representing a globally recognized media business in their search for an interim Financial Controller.\n\nThe role is reporting into the CFO and will take full control of the financial data, managing a lean team and providing financial guidance to the business. This is very much a Financial Controller at an operating company level rather than pulling together group figures.Main responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Production of monthly board accounts including reconciliations and setting up the board report</li>\n \t<li>Ensuring deadlines are met for group reporting, including monthly, quarterly forecasting and budgeting</li>\n \t<li>Manage the AP/AR functions</li>\n \t<li>Responsible for statutory accounts</li>\n \t<li>Analyse the business KPI’s and provide guidance to senior leadership</li>\n \t<li>Offer assistance for the upcoming finance transformation project</li>\n \t<li>Take ownership of internal controls and financial procedures, ensuring they are all up to date and correct</li>\n</ul>\nIdeal Candidate:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant ACA/ACCA/ACMA or equivalent</li>\n \t<li>Experience in a senior financial-management role,</li>\n \t<li>Experience with SOX preferable</li>\n \t<li>Prior experience managing AP, AR etc</li>\n \t<li>Ideally some media/marketing/advertising experience</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CH0232"},
  {title: "Group Finance Manager", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 60000, description: "This highly recognised and hugely successful group with their HQ in London are now looking for a talented Group Finance Manager to join the ranks at one of their fastest growing and successful consumer focussed brands. The environment isn’t for everyone, it takes a lot of energy and hard-work to push the business and maintain top spot in their industry. However, with hard work comes reward and further opportunities and responsibilities realistic to expectations.\n\nYou are wholly responsible for the day to day accounting and financial management of the brand. Providing financial support to the operations team, you will also produce accurate financial reports and develop viable strategies through financial and commercial research.\n\nInternally, you are a key contact to the C-suite, as well as Commercial, Operational, and Brand Directors. You will also have external relationships with Auditors, HMRC, Tax Advisors, business suppliers and lenders.Main responsibilities include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Day to day finance support to operations</li>\n \t<li>Management of invoicing and credit control</li>\n \t<li>Relationship building with key suppliers</li>\n \t<li>Management and overseeing purchase ledger</li>\n \t<li>Payroll management</li>\n \t<li>Review of VAT returns</li>\n \t<li>Management of trial balance – accruals and pre-payments, balance sheet reconciliations, accounts, fixed assets and depreciations</li>\n \t<li>Production of management accounts</li>\n \t<li>Continuous review and improvement of processes</li>\n \t<li>Take ownership of accounting processes, driving efficiency to work flows</li>\n \t<li>Creating and improving monthly flash reports</li>\n \t<li>Leading monthly balance sheet reconciliations</li>\n \t<li>P&amp;L analysis</li>\n \t<li>Ability to present and talk through variances with senior level execs</li>\n \t<li>Supporting statutory accounting processes for a listed business</li>\n \t<li>Assist with IFRS/UK GAAP compliance</li>\n \t<li>Implement operational accounting initiatives</li>\n \t<li>Assist and manage commercial projects from a finance perspective</li>\n \t<li>Annual audit activities</li>\n</ul>\nIt is clear from the above that you will be hugely proficient with the daily elements and cycle routines of finance. You’ll be Qualified ACA/ACCA/CIMA. You’ll definitely have strong IT and modelling skills and you’ll certainly have exposure to responsibilities of a similar nature.", responsibilities: nil, location: "London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "DN231"},
  {title: "Commercial Accounting Manager", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 55000, description: "A hotel group is looking for a Commercial Accounting Manager to join their head office team to provide insight into business performance through analysis of KPI’s and results. The Commercial Accounting Manager will business partner with non-finance teams to support with the P&amp;L, providing short to long term strategic decision support.\n\n<strong>Key responsibilities: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>New system implementation including review and improvement</li>\n \t<li>Budgeting and forecasting</li>\n \t<li>Business partnering with Marketing, Revenue, HR and Operations</li>\n \t<li>Revenue forecasting &amp; reporting</li>\n \t<li>Daily, weekly &amp; monthly operational stats preparation</li>\n \t<li>Reporting performance</li>\n \t<li>Contributing to ongoing revenue strategy</li>\n \t<li>Design and implement processes and controls</li>\n \t<li>Reporting revenue stats</li>\n \t<li>Accounting review</li>\n \t<li>Dealing with Operational suppliers &amp; ensuring correct accounting balances on supplier accounts as well as correct amount invoiced</li>\n \t<li>Weekly review of Operational supplier positions and invoicing</li>\n \t<li>Audit of franchisees</li>\n \t<li>Automation &amp; process improvements</li>\n \t<li>Full &amp; Half Year Results &amp; Audit PLC/UK Ltd – Involvement</li>\n</ul><strong>Key requirements: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant – (ACCA / CIMA / ACA)</li>\n \t<li>Good management accounts expereince</li>\n \t<li>Previous experience business partnering with different head of departments.</li>\n</ul>\nIf you are looking for an exciting commercial business partnering role working for a global FTSE business then please apply now.", responsibilities: nil, location: "London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0023"},
  {title: "Finance Manager", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Mining, Energy & Oil & Gas", salary: 85000, description: "Working in oil and gas can be relentlessly busy and hard work, hours can be up and down (mainly up) and keeping on top of regulations can be a headache at the best of times. On the flip side, it certainly has its benefits. You have a variety of working environments and global locations open to you, you can potentially progress very quickly through the ranks and there will always be plenty of training and development offered to you. Let’s also not forget you will generally have access to the most up to date technology available.\n\n&nbsp;This international and recognised oil and gas company are now looking for a Finance Manager to manage and lead a team in London. Having been in business for a number of decades, they work mainly on upstream projects but also have some involvement in mid and downstream. On the surface they look like a slick outfit – professional, intelligent and commercially minded people behind the helm and a strong, steady growth pattern over the decades. Scratch beneath the surface and you see much the same in most areas of the business.\n\n<strong>So why the need for the job?</strong>\n\nThe finance team comprise of some very talented individuals and generally the department is ran relatively well. What they need is a commercially minded individual that can ‘connect the dots’ and be able to create a higher level of accuracy, better communication cross-departmentally and can understand how to better the process from Head Office all the way down to the ground level subsidiaries. Naturally, that also means you can communicate incredibly well and get your point across to C-suite and high level directors.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Main responsibilities:</strong>\n\nManagement and development of a team of 6 (Qualified and Part-qualified level)\n\nResponsibility for the general accounting piece for up to 60 companies in the group\n\nInter-company recharges\n\nMonth/Quarter end processes\n\nMonthly management accounts\n\nCash flow forecasting\n\nYear-end management and liaising with auditors\n\nFinancial statements", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "DN232"},
  {title: "Finance Analyst", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 45000, description: "An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly numerate and analytical individual to join a gambling organisation as a Finance Analyst. As the Finance Analyst you will be responsible for providing high quality analytics and insight across the business areas internationally.\n\n&nbsp;<strong>Key responsibilities: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Preparation of KPI dashboards and reports</li>\n \t<li>Identifying key business trends and insights</li>\n \t<li>Market share report preparation</li>\n \t<li>Business performance information preparation and presentation</li>\n \t<li>Analyse and report on demand, staffing and labour activity</li>\n \t<li>Analyse gaming operations and efficency</li>\n \t<li>Customer segment trend reporting</li>\n \t<li>Revenue reporting</li>\n \t<li>Probability modelling</li>\n \t<li>Profitability and market spend analysis</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Key requirements: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Numerical undergraduate degree 2:1 minimum achievement</li>\n \t<li>Ability to understand, interpret and communicate complex data</li>\n \t<li>Advanced Excel skills and working knowledge of microsfot applications</li>\n \t<li>A solid understanding of statistics and probability</li>\n \t<li>Highly numerate with strong analytical skills</li>\n \t<li>High attention to detail</li>\n \t<li>An understanding of casino games would be beneficial but not essential.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you are looking for an opportunity to learn in a finance analyst role working for a leading gaming and gambling organisation then pleasae apply now!", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0024"},
  {title: "Senior Accountant / Finance Manager - 3 Month Contract", job_type: "contract", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 350, description: "We are currently partnering with a luxury retail SME who are incredibly well thought of within their industry. This is an exciting business who are looking for a Senior Accountant/ Finance manager to report directly into the CFO and help run the day to day finance function. They will work closely with the Directors, investors and all the non-finance divisions too.\n\nThis is a very fast pace business who are in a rapid period of growth and looking to continue.Main responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Take accountability for the day-to-day finance function</li>\n \t<li>Take ownership of the cash flow forecast, updating on a monthly basis</li>\n \t<li>Oversee the production of management accounts and additional commentary</li>\n \t<li>Prepare quarterly KPI's</li>\n \t<li>Manage a small team of AP &amp; AR</li>\n</ul>\nIdeal Candidate:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified Accountant</li>\n \t<li>Strong all-round finance and accounting experience</li>\n \t<li>Previous small company or start up exposure</li>\n \t<li>Previous experience ideally within fashion or luxury retail</li>\n \t<li>Ability to interact with non-finance and investors</li>\n \t<li>Strong people management experience</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "Shoreditch ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CH0233"},
  {title: "Group Systems Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 65000, description: "A property organisation is looking for a group systems accountant to join their team based in Central London. As the Systems Accountant you will be responsible for both maintenance, implementation and continuous improvement of all system accounting.Key responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Financial System and Process Enhancement</li>\n \t<li>Point of contact for information requests and business support</li>\n \t<li>Maintain relationships with external suppliers</li>\n \t<li>Month end system close</li>\n \t<li>Create and maintain system documentation including process flows and training materials</li>\n \t<li>Produce cross functional reporting solutions and manage the interface with IT</li>\n \t<li>Identify opportunities for system improvements and manage the development and implementation</li>\n \t<li>Dive process change and management</li>\n \t<li>Finance related project management, including Oracle upgrade and integration</li>\n</ul>\nKey Requirements:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified Accountant (ACCA / CIMA) essential</li>\n \t<li>Previous experience in system maintenance, functionality and problem fixing is essential</li>\n \t<li>Experience in driving change and improvement projects as well as change management is essential</li>\n \t<li>Project Management (Prince 2 etc) is desirable</li>\n \t<li>A dynamic and personable individual with the ability to effectively drive change</li>\n \t<li>Multiple systems experience including Oracle would be beneficial</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0025"},
  {title: "Finance Analyst", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 45000, description: "An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly numerate and analytical individual to join a gambling organisation as a Finance Analyst. As the Finance Analyst you will be responsible for providing high quality analytics and insight across the business areas internationally.<strong>Key responsibilities: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Preparation of KPI dashboards and reports</li>\n \t<li>Identifying key business trends and insights</li>\n \t<li>Market share report preparation</li>\n \t<li>Business performance information preparation and presentation</li>\n \t<li>Analyse and report on demand, staffing and labour activity</li>\n \t<li>Analyse gaming operations and efficency</li>\n \t<li>Customer segment trend reporting</li>\n \t<li>Revenue reporting</li>\n \t<li>Probability modelling</li>\n \t<li>Profitability and market spend analysis</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Key requirements: </strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Numerical undergraduate degree 2:1 minimum achievement</li>\n \t<li>Ability to understand, interpret and communicate complex data</li>\n \t<li>Advanced Excel skills and working knowledge of microsfot applications</li>\n \t<li>A solid understanding of statistics and probability</li>\n \t<li>Highly numerate with strong analytical skills</li>\n \t<li>High attention to detail</li>\n \t<li>An understanding of casino games would be beneficial but not essential.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you are looking for an opportunity to learn in a finance analyst role working for a leading gaming and gambling organisation then please apply now!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;", responsibilities: nil, location: "London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0026"},
  {title: "Financial Controller", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 70000, description: "This is a newly created position within a rapid growth, international communications consultancy based in the city. This is a key position tasked with providing strong leadership to the finance team as well as improving and maintaining processes and controls.Key Responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Ownership of management accounting function, reporting on 6 entities</li>\n \t<li>Production of monthly board pack</li>\n \t<li>Ability to advise on improvements to board pack and streamline reporting</li>\n \t<li>Produce group cashflow forecast each quarter</li>\n \t<li>Updating of budgets on monthly basis to ensure accurate forecasts for YE result</li>\n \t<li>Responsibility for production of annual budgets and forecasts for each entity &amp; group consolidated budget as part of the annual business planning process</li>\n \t<li>Review and update management account process unsure adequate system &amp; templates in place</li>\n \t<li>First point of contact with Group auditors</li>\n \t<li>Will need to take ownership of audit process with production of full &amp; complete audit files/financial statements for all group entities</li>\n \t<li>Identifying opportunities for cost saving</li>\n \t<li>Cover for FD when necessary</li>\n</ul>\nFinancial Controller Candidate Requirements:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified accountant with at least 2 years PQE (CIMA/ACCA/ACA)</li>\n \t<li>Netsuite is an advantage</li>\n \t<li>Strong management skills</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London  ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "BFJ0421"},
  {title: "Corporate Finance Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 45000, description: "<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">We are currently searching for finalist level ACCA/CIMA to join an international business as a Corporate Finance Accountant.</p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"></p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"></p><p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b><u>The Role</u></b></p>\n\n<ul type=\"disc\">\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Management accounts</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Balance sheet reconciliations</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Assisting with the analysis of spend across Marketing and IT</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Assist and be a point of contact in the annual audit</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Assist with budgeting and reforecasting</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Ad hoc project work as requested by the Corporate finance manager</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"></p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b><u>The Opportunity</u></b></p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">The truly exciting part about this role is ‘The opportunity’. At the point where you are Finalist and so eager to take on more responsibility and prove yourself you may feel too harnessed. This business are looking for that person that is hungry to take on more responsibility than the day to days printed on a Job Description.</p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">They need someone proactive and someone that wants to make an impact!</p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"></p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\"><b><u>Profile</u></b></p>\n\n<ul type=\"disc\">\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Finalist- ACCA/CIMA</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Excellent communication - your communication across the business will be varied in terms of seniority</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Enthusiasm - they need someone who will on a daily basis be enthusiastic to learn and progress</li>\n \t<li class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\">Adaptable - this business is ever growing and ever changing so you must be able to deal with change</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "JC01253"},
  {title: "Interim Group Accountant", job_type: "contract", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 400, description: "A Multi-national manufacturing business is looking to set up its group finance function in London and needs some interim support.\n\nYou will be responsible for consolidation and reporting of the regional units with the analysis of the financial information and advisory on development and deviations to executive management. You will also supervise the off-site accounting for the regional entities, as well as working with our manufacturing entities in ensuring reports, analysis and financial processes are accurate and in place for the Group.<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Group consolidation of the regional entities under IFRS and US-GAAP standards</li>\n \t<li>Update and maintain accounting standards (accounting manuals) centrally for the group under IFRS</li>\n \t<li>Support auditors during the annual auditing process</li>\n \t<li>Prepare the periodic financial reports with variance analysis and commentaries to the management team and ability to oversee the data for completeness &amp; consistency, challenge it when appropriate and prepare corrections together with the regional teams and consolidate the regional data packs in Hyperion</li>\n \t<li>Advise and train the regional and country teams in correct use of accounts and the technical treatment of transactions in Hyperion.</li>\n \t<li>Interprets and communicates financial data to non-financial managers</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Key Skills</strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA, ACCA, CIMA qualified</li>\n \t<li>Experience of operating in an international Finance function, preferably in a medium to large matrix structure</li>\n \t<li>Experience in preparing consolidated reports under the IFRS and US-GAAP standards</li>\n \t<li>A high level of numeracy and IT proficiency with strong skills in Hyperion</li>\n \t<li>Ability to provide training in Hyperion and guidance on accounting standards to the regional Finance teams</li>\n \t<li>Ability to maintain and establish and maintain strong relationships with business leaders, across the Regional Finance teams and with non-Finance members of staff</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "HS0421"},
  {title: "Senior Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Infrastructure & Prof. Services", salary: 65000, description: "<p style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: #333333;\">Work/life balance and flexible hours are becoming more common place nowadays and this role certainly offers that. It also offers a competitive salary and up to 20% bonus.</span></p><p style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: #333333;\">This company is renowned for looking after its staff and you’ll find the reviews from past and current employees are excellent. It would come as no surprise that the company also does particularly well in business. Well let’s give them more credit than that, they do incredibly well - they made three times more profit than anticipated last year. That’s outstanding in whatever industry you work in and for the company to perform at this level, their employees have to work collectively and they have to work hard. Very hard.</span></p>\n<p style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: #333333;\">This job is definitely not easy. It will test you and challenge you on a daily basis. You need to stay sharp, focused and results driven. But you’re not on your own, you’ll find that you’re supported by a very high-performing team that consistently achieves. The finance department you will be joining is a slick outfit with incredible team ethic.</span></p>\n<p style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: #333333;\">In terms of your every day duties, essentially you will be responsible for the accounting and analysis for the group wide revenue. With the help of your analysts, you will produce accurate accounting for revenue and costs. Your modelling skills will help create new schemes and ensure better accuracy and you will have excellent communication skills so you can form close working relationships with key stakeholders and senior management staff across the business. You also need to be an effective team manager and know how to motivate and get the best out of your team.</span></p>\n<p style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: 'Helvetica',sans-serif; color: #333333;\">This role will require a career driven and qualified accountant. In return, you will be offered a competitive salary, excellent bonuses, flexible working, a strong team supporting you and a company that regularly exceeds expectation.</span></p>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "DN234"},
  {title: "Senior Financial Accountant", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 65000, description: "This is a superb opportunity to join a fast growth, listed Technology business based in Central London.\n\nThe role is diverse and will provide the next step if you are currently confined to statutory reporting alone.<strong><u>Key responsibilities will include: </u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Management Accounts</li>\n \t<li>Forecasting/ budgeting and providing valuable comment on key business drivers</li>\n \t<li>Statutory reporting (IFRS)</li>\n \t<li>Variance analysis</li>\n \t<li>Balance sheet reconciliations and analysis</li>\n \t<li>Risk management and contributing towards the maintenance of strong internal controls (including SOX)</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><u>The opportunity</u></strong>\n\nThis is an opportunity to join a business that put their employee’s development at the forefront of priority.\n\nThis role will work closely with an extremely accomplished Finance Director and wider team.\n\nThe culture is superb! It is dress down, innovative and most importantly an outstanding product. They are looking for forward thinkers with an ability to challenge the status quo, so if you are looking to join a business where your ideas are valued and implemented this could also be you!\n\n<strong><u>What you will need; </u></strong>\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA/ ACCA qualified in practice</li>\n \t<li>Knowledge of IFRS/ US GAAP/ SOX</li>\n \t<li>Exposure working with an ERP system</li>\n \t<li>A methodical approach</li>\n \t<li>Strong communication skills</li>\n \t<li>Multi-currency reporting would be preferable</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "JC1254"},
  {title: "Financial Controller - Luxury Fashion Retail", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 60000, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently partnering with a high-growth, luxury fashion retailer based in West London to help recruit for a Financial Controller position to join as the number one in finance for the organisation. This role will be responsible for leading the finance function, as well as taking on responsibility for day to day operations.\n\nThis person will be getting involved both in the detail and will also be required to \"roll up their sleeves\". They will also be getting involved in high level work - including financial planning, budgeting, forecasting and analysing trends.Some of the responsibilities for the role include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Managing company accounts and management accounts</li>\n \t<li>Managing cash flow for the business</li>\n \t<li>Partnering with non-finance and working closely with the leadership team for the business</li>\n \t<li>Processing and paying invoices</li>\n \t<li>Reporting to the CEO and Board Members with timely and accurate financial information</li>\n \t<li>Suggesting updates and improvements to accounting systems</li>\n \t<li>General process improvement mindset as this person will be leading improvements to the finance function across the organisation</li>\n</ul>\nThe ideal candidate profile for the position will be:\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA/ACCA/CIMA Qualified</li>\n \t<li>Experience working in a small business and dealing with the challenges and opportunities that this involves</li>\n \t<li>Experience working within the retail/fashion/luxury space is a must have</li>\n \t<li>Strong organisational skills, as well as time management</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "West London", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "AM0514"},
  {title: "Commercial Finance Analyst - 3 - 6 months", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 325, description: "Global Accounting Network are currently representing a rapidly growing, PE backed business in London. They are subscription based with incredibly loyal customers who offer high levels of repeat revenues.\n\n&nbsp;The client requires a Commercial Finance Analyst for 3-6 months, with a potential for the role to go temp to perm.\n\nThe Commercial Finance Analyst will report into the Commercial Finance Manager, but also have exposure into a private-equity environment and PE stakeholders.\n\nMain responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Maintain and develop weekly flash trading reports</li>\n \t<li>Produce the relevant analysis on the trade reports to present in the weekly trade meeting</li>\n \t<li>Produce monthly board reports and assist with investment papers</li>\n \t<li>Business partner across the group to assist in the preparation of the group’s budgeting and forecasting process</li>\n \t<li>Continuously drive improvements in both processes and policies to allow more informed business decisions to be made</li>\n \t<li>Ad hoc responsibilities and projects. (External financing and M&amp;A)</li>\n</ul>\nIdeal background:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified Accountant with some industry experience</li>\n \t<li>Ideally retail or e-commerce experience</li>\n \t<li>Ability to build relationships with both finance and non-finance, internal and external stakeholders</li>\n \t<li>Strong excel and ideally SQL knowledge</li>\n \t<li>Ability to work autonomously and pick things up quickly</li>\n</ul>", responsibilities: nil, location: "Central London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CH0234"},
  {title: "Group Financial Accountant - 6 month contract", job_type: "contract", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 350, description: "An FMCG organisation is currently looking to hire an interim group financial accountant on a 6 month basis. The role is sitting in their finance team supporting with preparing financial statements and doing group consolidations.Key responsibilities include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Preparation of monthly consolidated group results and reporting to investors.</li>\n \t<li>Financial reporting including compliance</li>\n \t<li>Support with external audits including planning and delivery.</li>\n \t<li>Group support in technical accounting matters</li>\n \t<li>Partner non-finance staff on the accounting impact of business decisions</li>\n</ul>\nKey requirements include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Qualified Accountant, Big 4 ACA or CA equivalent</li>\n \t<li>Previous experience within FMCG , Consumer Goods or Retail is desirable</li>\n \t<li>Strong communication and stakeholder engagement</li>\n \t<li>Experience in doing group consolidations is essential</li>\n \t<li>Ability to work autonomously</li>\n \t<li>Very strong technical accounting skills including experience and knowledge of IFRS</li>\n</ul>\nIf you have the requirements listed and are looking for an interesting financial accountant role then please apply now", responsibilities: nil, location: "West London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0027F"},
  {title: "Financial Accountant 3-6 months", job_type: "contract", sector: "Technology, Media & Telecoms", salary: 350, description: "A leading consumer organisation is looking for an interim Financial Accountant to support them on a 3-6month interim period during a period of exciting change and development. They are looking for a bright and collaborative qualified accountant with experience in IFRS and Statutory reporting who is able to confidently hit the ground running.Key responsibilities:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Complete statutory financial statements according to IFRS guidelines</li>\n \t<li>Delivery Financial Reporting to the Group</li>\n \t<li>Manage treasury operation and cash flow management</li>\n \t<li>Reporting and submission of financial plans and forecasts</li>\n \t<li>Calculate and match HR related accruals</li>\n \t<li>Ensure internal processes are defined and compliant</li>\n \t<li>Transfer pricing</li>\n \t<li>Tax</li>\n</ul>\nKey requirements:\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA Qualified</li>\n \t<li>2+ years post qualified experience</li>\n \t<li>Proven experience in producing statutory accounts</li>\n \t<li>Knowledge of IFRS reporting guidelines</li>\n \t<li>Experience in using an ERP system is essential, SAP would be helpful</li>\n \t<li>Strong and competent SAP and PowerPoint user</li>\n</ul>\nThis is an exciting opportunity for an immediately available financial accountant and proven in working as an interim to work in a well renowned organisation during an exciting period of change. Please apply now for an ASAP call back!", responsibilities: nil, location: "West London ", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "CL0028"},
  {title: "Senior FP&A Manager / Finance Business Partner - Global Pharma", job_type: "permament_full_time", sector: "Retail, FMCG & Hospitality", salary: 95000, description: "Global Accounting Network are recruiting for a US listed pharmaceutical business, who have displayed incredible growth over the past decade due to phenomenal progression and development around specific drugs and products.\n\nOur client is looking to hire a Senior Manager, FP&amp;A, which will be a business partner to key therapeutic areas across the EMEA region and will be the “go to person” for business analysis, insight and advice in their specific therapeutic area.\n\nThis person will also act as the lead Opex business partner to the EMEA VP Commercial Planning.Some of their key responsibilities will include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Working with EMEA Finance and non-Finance leads, as well as Commercial Analysts to provide insight around business trends and developments</li>\n \t<li>Managing and preparing financial planning, reporting and analysis for various functions</li>\n \t<li>Acting as a key conduit and link between non-finance and the controllership function</li>\n \t<li>Developing new analytical tools to support business decisions within markets and across the EMEA region</li>\n</ul>\nThe ideal candidate will have:\n<ul>\n \t<li>ACA/ACCA/CIMA qualification</li>\n \t<li>Strong academic background</li>\n \t<li>Proven track record of business partnering with non-finance functions and driving results</li>\n \t<li>Extensive experience in Corporate FP&amp;A, with a strong understanding of the planning cycle</li>\n \t<li>Experience of working within large, listed company environments and an understanding of the complexities, challenges and opportunities in these businesses</li>\n \t<li>A natural bias for data, and data analytics, with the ability to provide insights into business performance</li>\n</ul>\nThis is a fantastic opportunity to join an exciting and innovative organisation, who are notorious in their space for creating a slick and fast-paced environment.", responsibilities: nil, location: "Uxbridge/Hounslow", company_id: nil, company_job_alerts: false, job_function: nil, ref_id: "AM0515"}
